            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Good condition. The naos and narthex of Asinou contain numerous cryptograms that have been previously discussed in literature (<bibl><ptr target="#Rhoby2009"/>,<citedRange> 344-5</citedRange></bibl>; <bibl><ptr target="#Ševčenko2012"/>,<citedRange> 84-5</citedRange></bibl>; <bibl><ptr target="#Kalopissi-Verti2012"/>,<citedRange>190-2</citedRange></bibl>; <bibl><ptr target="#MoutafovRhoby2012"/>,<citedRange> 181-7</citedRange></bibl>). This particular cryptic inscription has not yet been deciphered. Sacopoulou reconstructed the letters AΠΜC and proposed to read them as follows: Ἀδὰμ Πεπτωκὼς Μετέστη Σταυρὸν (<bibl><ptr target="#Sacopoulo1966"/>,<citedRange> 112</citedRange></bibl>).</p>
            </div>
